---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/page/PageHero.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Verify | Virtual Ventures"
  description="Pattern verification notes for Virtual Ventures pattern IDs, QR codes, versions and official updates."
  showFooterBreadcrumbs={false}
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Official Source"
    title="Verify"
    description="Check whether a Virtual Ventures pattern, QR code, PDF or printed collection points back to the official source."
  />

  <main class="page-shell">
    <section class="page-intro">
      <p class="eyebrow">Pattern verification</p>
      <h1>Follow the official thread</h1>
      <p>
        Pattern verification pages help readers confirm they are using the real
        Virtual Ventures source, especially when a pattern was found through a
        marketplace, social post, printed QR code or shared link.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>What to check</h2>
        <p>
          A Virtual Ventures pattern may include a pattern ID, version number,
          update date and QR code. Those details should point to the official
          Virtual Ventures website.
        </p>
        <p>
          Example pattern ID format: [VV-PATTERN-ID]. Example verification URL:
          /verify/[pattern-id]/.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-right">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>What a future pattern page should show</h2>
        <p>
          Each future verification page should show the pattern title, pattern
          ID, current version, latest update date, official free pattern link,
          optional PDF link, known corrections and any important safety notes.
        </p>
        <p>
          If there is no matching verification page yet, check the main pattern
          page or contact Virtual Ventures before trusting a suspicious download.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-section content-left">
      <article class="content-card">
        <h2>Suspicious copies</h2>
        <p>
          If a listing or file removes the Virtual Ventures name, changes the QR
          code, hides the pattern ID, uses Virtual Ventures photos, or sells a
          copied free pattern as its own download, please report it.
        </p>
        <p>
          Reporting page: <a href="/report-stolen-pattern/">Report a Copy</a>.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-closing-card">
      <p>
        Verification pages are little signposts back to the real workshop door.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
